From afb8b95f5fd6ab3996aec0f4c1609ae721378982 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 05:28:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] landing: add real color coding + decorative hero
 background (match reference)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Addresses visual gaps vs the reference design:

- Test category cards, stat tiles, and why-choose cards were all
  rendering in a single flat teal, whereas the reference uses a
  distinct pastel color per item (blue/purple/orange/red/teal/amber).
  Added bg/fg color fields to the component's data arrays and bound
  them via [style.background]/[style.color] on the icon circles.
- Stats band had no icons at all (design reference shows a colored
  icon above each number) — added icon markup + per-stat color.
- Hero-right was flat mint green with no imagery, unlike the
  reference's blurred lab-photo background. Rather than pull in an
  external photo (licensing/availability risk), added a self-contained
  inline SVG decorative layer — blurred vial cluster + microscope
  silhouette — positioned behind the login card via z-index. No
  external asset dependency, nothing to break.

No changes to styles.css or any other route — landing page component
files only.
